Plugin : sslexplorer-radius
Version: 0.0.1

Provides
--------

* Configuration Page - RADIUS
* Authentication Method - RADIUS

Note: If you are going to use an Active Directory user database. You will have
to configure a guest username / password so SSL-Explorer can retrieve user
accounts details. This is done using the conf/system.properties file. Edit the
following two properties :-

	1) sslexplorer.activeDirectory.guestUsername
	2) sslexplorer.activeDirectory.guestPassword


Building the plugin from source
-------------------------------

Requirements
------------

* SSL-Explorer 0.1.9 
* Apache Ant 1.6+
* Java 1.5 JDK.

Procedure
---------

1. If you havnt done so already, install 0.1.9.

2. Copy the provided build.properties.sample to build.properties in the 
   same directory.
   
3. Edit build.properties and change sslexplorer.home to be location of
   your SSL-Explorer installation.
   
4. Run the default ant target, e.g.

   $ ant 
   
5. If all goes well, you will have a zip file in build/archive. Unzip 
   the file into [sslexplorer.home]/conf/extensions and restart the
   server.
   
